The paper deals with geometric network design problems, specifically the problem of computing longest non-crossing configurations of straight line segments in the plane. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also presents approximation algorithms for these problems, which involves analyzing the structure of the geometric network, and hence could be classified under data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also uses graph theory concepts such as Hamiltonian paths and cycles, which could be classified under graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper presents algorithms with running time analysis, which could be classified under algorithms and data structures (cs.SI).
